article.headline: Stephen F. Austin 71, McNeese St. 43
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Taylor Smith had 15 points, grabbed 14 rebounds and Stephen F. Austin shot 55.1 percent from the field in a 71-43 blowout over McNeese State on Saturday night. Stephen F. Austin (12-1, 3-0 Southland) held the Cowboys to just 31.9 percent shooting and out-rebounded them 41-25. The Lumberjacks led 23-19 at halftime but shot 66.7 percent in the second half, making 18 of 27 shots and outscoring the Cowboys 48-24. Antonio Bostic scored 15 points for Stephen F. Austin, Jacob Parker had 14 and Thomas Walkup added 11. The Lumberjacks were 16 of 30 from the free-throw line in the game. Desharick Guidry had 12 points and eight rebounds to lead McNeese State (6-6, 0-2). Guidry gave the Cowboys their only lead of the night when he made it 2-0 to start the game but Stephen F. Austin answered with an 11-0 run and never trailed again.
